default3.2default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn carrying out this role, it would be important for the 
defaultDfT
default to ensure that its interventions are proportionate, and that (subject to meetings its performance specification) the HA has sufficient flexibility to foster the benefits of greater commercialism.
defaultIdefaultncentives and enforcementdefault3.3default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFor the majority of companies, shareholders 
defaultstand to gain financially where the company is able to become more efficient. Hence, shareholders 
defaultexert pressure on management to achieve efficiencies.
default 
defaultThe HA’s sole shareholder will be the government, which means that these pressures are unlikely to be replicated fully. Consideration will therefore have to be given to how management can best be incentivised to achieve efficiencies. This is closely linked to how the new company, and its management, is held to account for its performance—in particular, what penalties would arise if the company were to fail (continually) to meet the terms of the performance specification? 
default3.4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThese issues are not unique to the roads sector—
defaultindeed,
default they have vexed the GB rail industry given Network Rail’s non-conventional corporate structure.
default 
defaultIn the rail sector, management incentives have been provided by linking pay to the performance of the company relative to regulatory measures of performance. Indeed, for there to be efficiency incentives similar to those in an equity-financed company, the 
defaultDfT
default will have to influence the HA’s board. Performance-related pay is likely to be one of the simplest and most effective means of providing incentives at the board level. However, the 
defaultDfT
default will need to consider how it can design the licence to limit any disconnect between the level of senior bonuses and its assessment of the HA’s performance. 
default3.5default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultExperience from other sectors suggests that, as well as performance-related pay, the following arrangements could be considered.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLinking the level of funding to the delivery of certain performance metricsdefault. 
defaultFor example, funding coul
defaultd be withheld if the HA fails
default to meets its performance targets.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProvide reputational incentivesdefault.
default For non-equity companies, reputational incentives can be strong motivators. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSpecial administration arrangementsdefault.
default Arrangements could be put in place to allow the 
defaultDfT
default to remove and replace the senior management team at the HA, either if certain predefined thresholds are breached or at the discretion of the Secretary of State for Transport. The threat of such arrangements being enforced would provide strong incentives to the HA management team.
default3.6default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn addition, the 
defaultDfT
default has indicated that it is looking at options for a road user ‘watchdog’ or ‘champion’. Such a body would be expected to monitor the new company’s performance and identify if it is failing to meet targets. This might include periodically benchmarking the company’s costs and efficiency relative to other UK infrastructure managers and international road companies. More broadly, the watchdog or champion would act as the voice of the road user, ensuring that road users’ priorities are reflected in the HA’s decision-making processes.
default3.7default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSetting up a watchdog or consumer champion would be expected to enhance the reputational incentives for management to exert effort. Indeed, t
defaulthe likelihood is that the body’s publication of performance figures would, over time, receive widespread media attention (as is the case with information on Network Rail’s performance), providing further 
defaultincentive for management to ensure that the company meets its targets. The watchdog could also play a role if funding were to be linked to meeting performance standards (
defaulteg
default, funding could be linked to the number of complaints received by the watchdog).
defaultUncertainty mechanismsdefault3.8default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 
defaultfinancial discipline required from the new company will change from that under the current model
default. If the 
defaultDfT
default steps in to provide additional funding where the 
defaultHA
default is being inefficiently operated, efficiency incentive
defaults will be considerably weakened. To the extent possible, therefore, the HA needs to operate under a hard budget constraint.
default3.9default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere is, however, also a risk that factors beyond the control of the management team will create a situation where the company is unable to meet the terms of the performance specification under the existing funding settlement. This could, for example, be the result of an external shock that leads to the HA facing significantly higher costs than previously forecast. There is thus a trade-off between establishing a ‘hard’ budget constraint, thereby providing strong efficiency incentives, and ensuring that there is flexibility to respond to changing circumstances within the funding period.
default3.10default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt may therefore be necessary to specify the circumstances under which the HA can ask for additional funding (or a reduced performance specification), and to outline the appeals process, should the company find that it cannot live with a settlement. There are well-established practices from economic regulation of other infrastructure sectors in the UK that can be applied to provide the new company and its management with appropriate safeguards against non-controllable factors, while preserving efficiency incentives.
