defaultie
default, insurance and fuel costs). There is also evidence of a partial modal shift towards rail, particularly for business travel, given the reduction in company car usage.
default An understanding is 
defaultneeded of how cultural changes, particularly for young people, will affect future road demand.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultParking constraintsdefault.
default A potential weakness of the NTM is that it does not factor in constraints on the availability of parking spaces. Decisions on whether to make a car journey are likely to be heavily influenced by the ability to park at the destination. Consequently, better understanding is needed of how the availability of parking spaces will affect future road demand.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGreater geographic disaggregationdefault.
default For decision-making purposes, there are likely to be clear benefits from having greater spatial detail on the breakdown of demand—for example, an understanding of the routes on which road traffic is likely to grow rapidly and where this could lead to congestion. 
